Enjoy part 1 as we drive through rivers & lava fields to see countless volcanos, waterfalls, & glaciers :) Use our link to get $20 off your first AG1 subscription or $49 off when you sign up for a double subscription just like we have! + 5 free travel packs and a bottle of Vitamin D3K2 :) Click: http://drinkag1.com/karaandnate

â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”

Who are Kara and Nate?! 
Watch our documentary here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FuFv4iF8wgg&t=1s 

Originally from Nashville, Tennessee, we got married 2013 and were super â€œnormal.â€ I was a teacher and Nate started a small printing business from the spare bedroom of our apartment. 

We discovered the world of â€œtravel hackingâ€ while planning our honeymoon & became addicted ;)

So after 2 years of obsessively saving $35k and over 2 million miles and points, we sold our cars and apartment and left home January 10, 2016 for a â€œone yearâ€ trip around the world.

Our goal was to see as many places as possible before we ran out of money and went back home to â€œnormal life.â€ We started this channel to share our experiences with friends and family, but quickly fell in love with living on the road and found a new passion for capturing our travels through video. So we did everything we could to keep going.

4 years later, we achieved our new goal of visiting 100 countries and all 7 continents. We had no plans to slow down, until 2020 forced us to ;) Which is when we bought a converted van to start exploring our own country for the first time!

After ~2 years of van life, we are back to full time international traveling! And now we are in our 9TH YEAR of finding the best adventures the world has to offer :) 

We are incredibly grateful to be able to continue doing something we love every day. ğŸ˜ŠğŸ¥ğŸŒ Thank you to everyone who has been a part of our journey!

4 years later, we achieved our new goal of visiting 100 countries and all 7 continents. We had no plans to slow down, until 2020 forced us to ;) Which is when we bought a converted van to start exploring our own country for the first time!

After ~2 years of van life, we are back to full time international traveling! And now we are in our 9TH YEAR of finding the best adventures the world has to offer :) 

We are incredibly grateful to be able to continue doing something we love every day. ğŸ˜ŠğŸ¥ğŸŒ Thank you to everyone who has been a part of our journey!

snippet.title: FIRST RIDE: Tesla Robotaxi â€“ Our Driverless Future Has Arrived!
snippet.description:
It's finally here: Elon Musk has revealed his long-awaited autonomous Tesla Robotaxi â€“ also referred to as the Cybercab â€“ at an event in Los Angeles, USA.

Looking a lot like the VW XL1 (remember that?) the Robotaxi has no steering wheel or pedals and just two seats. As the name suggests, its crisp flat surfaces and full-width light bars have more than a passing resemblance to the Cybertruck, too.

This, then, is Musk's vision of a grand autonomous future, and he promises the Robotaxi will be in full production by 2026, with prices starting from $30,000.

A fleet of 20 fully functioning prototypes were built to run around the Warner Bros. Studio lot â€“ the venue for Muskâ€™s big reveal â€“ and take passengers on short, obstacle-laden routes. Top Gear duly hailed one, so join our Editor-in-Chief, Jack Rix, for a first ride in the new Tesla Robotaxiâ€¦

Follow DAX: @thatsdax

Produced by: Lex Nour Beats

#lonelydirtroad #dax #dirtroad #driving #manhood 

Lyrics:

When I need space thatâ€™s where I go
A place to escape that nobody knows 
Where I feel free to let things go
And face this evil that burdens my soul
I bring my hatred, I pack my pain
All the emotions I cannot explain
Itâ€™s where I found God
And filled that whole
Itâ€™s he, myself and I
On that lonely dirt road


I needed somewhere to take my mistakes
I didnâ€™t want my family to see me cry
Theyâ€™ll never know Iâ€™m 
carrying all of this weight 
Dealing with the pressure 
of trying to provide
No sign of struggle can show on my face
They ask if Iâ€™m OK I just flash them a smile
Fire up that engine to take me away
Iâ€™m speeding through emotions with every mile
On that road is where I find my peace
I remember daddy told me about some times like these
On that road is where my minds at ease
I keep driving life away, rejecting change so

A place to escape that nobody knows 
Where I feel free to let things go
And face this evil that burdens my soul
I bring my hatred, I pack my pain
All the emotions I cannot explain
Itâ€™s where I found God
And filled that whole
Itâ€™s he, myself and I
On that lonely dirt road


I tried my best to plant the seeds
And then I watered everything that was in my life
But as a man, the only flowers that you get
Are when youâ€™re 6 feet under on the day you die
I think I feel the pain my father felt
Itâ€™s finally sinking in 
looking back all I see is his eyes
He said that house is not a home
Unless you build it on respect 
with some kids and a loving wife
If these walls could talk
I bet theyâ€™d say itâ€™s all my fault
That I donâ€™t try hard
That I ainâ€™t man enough
That I ainâ€™t standing up
That I just burn everything 
that my hands touch
If these walls could talk
I bet theyâ€™d say Iâ€™m to blame
That Iâ€™m the one who put myself inside of all of these chains
That my addictive personalities what ran them away
And that I hurt myself by staying quiet
And not explaining Iâ€™m broken
In places, I canâ€™t even see
I know thereâ€™s gotta be a heaven
Because the hell thatâ€™s in me
Is taking a dangerous toll
That Iâ€™m paying with all of my soul

A place to escape that nobody knows

And face this evil that burdens my soul

Itâ€™s he, myself and I
On that lonely dirt road

If you made it this deep you're a real one. Thank you for continuing to allow me to use my platform to make an impact. Your support is appreciated more than you'll ever know and I will continue to prove that with my actions. I'm very excited. 2024 is going to bring our best and most impactful work. I am putting everything into creating pieces we can all be proud of. This is music for the PEOPLE, spread BY THE PEOPLE. Like, comment, share and let's continue to be the change we wish to see in the world.

If you made it this deep you're a real one. Thank you for continuing to allow me to use my platform to make an impact. Your support is appreciated more than you'll ever know and I will continue to prove that with my actions. I'm very excited. 2024 is going to bring our best and most impactful work. I am putting everything into creating pieces we can all be proud of. This is music for the PEOPLE, spread BY THE PEOPLE. Like, comment, share and let's continue to be the change we wish to see in the world.

snippet.title: SURVIVING HURRICANE MILTON - A DEVASTATING STORM EXPERIENCE
snippet.description:
Hurricane Milton is the second major hurricane to strike Florida in two weeks, aggressively spinning up to a Category 5 storm in the Gulf of Mexico before making landfall in Sarasota Wednesday night. Milton brought insurmountable storm surge, flooding rains, and produced countless tornadoes which ravaged throughout Florida. This was our experience in Orlando.

Though we suffered a bit of property damage and a sleepless night, feeling very thankful that was the extent of our damages. Our hearts go out to all those affected on the coast; hopefully this is the last storm we have to deal with this year.

Follow us on social:

https://www.instagram.com/tmartn
https://www.twitter.com/chelseakreiner

snippet.title: 2000 Pound Table
snippet.description:

snippet.title: Joker: Folie Ã€ Deux Pitch Meeting
snippet.description:
Step inside the Pitch Meeting that led to Joker: Folie Ã€ Deux! 

Subscribe for more Pitch Meetings: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC9Kq-yEt1iYsbUzNOoIRK0g

Joker was kind of a surprise hit in 2019, becoming one of the most massive R-Rated movies of all time on a relatively small budget. Even though that movie was pretty self-contained, the market dictates that there MUST BE A SEQUEL. And here we are. There is one. It exists. And some choices were made.

So check out the pitch meeting that led to Joker: Folie Ã€ Deux to find out how it all came together!

snippet.title: Dog found in home rubble during live CBS report
snippet.description:
During a live report on CBS Mornings, Morgan Rynor from CBS News Miami and neighbors in Fort Pierce found a dog in the rubble of a home destroyed from Hurricane Milton. 

The owners sadly died in the storm but the dog survived and got out of the rubble.

snippet.title: Nintendo Sound Clock: Alarmo â€“ Announcement Trailer
snippet.description:
Introducing Nintendo Sound Clock: Alarmo, an interactive alarm clock thatâ€™s out of the ordinary! Alarmo responds to your bodyâ€™s movement with game sounds, so you can feel like youâ€™re waking up in the game world itself. Set an alarm inspired by five Nintendo games, with more alarms on the way as free updates as they become available. 

Add some play to the start of your day! 

Learn more: https://www.nintendo.com/us/store/products/nintendo-sound-clock-alarmo-121311/?utm_source=Other&utm_medium=soytnoa&utm_campaign=N0099-01&utm_id=N0099-01?utm_source=Other&utm_medium=soytnoa&utm_campaign=N0099-01&utm_id=N0099-01

For a limited time*, paid Nintendo Switch Online members in the United States and Canada can purchase Alarmo online via the My Nintendo Store before it is available to purchase by the general public. All visitors to the Nintendo New York store can purchase Nintendo Sound Clock: Alarmo in person at launch while supplies last.

*Early access available until early 2025 at the Nintendo NY store and online in the United States and Canada. Nintendo Account and paid Nintendo Switch Online membership required for online purchase during early access period.

snippet.title: Apex Legends: Techno Terror Collection Event Trailer
snippet.description:
Haunt your way through the Outlands with the return of Trick Nâ€™ Treat Trios with Revivals and more spine-chilling surprises! Use Copycat Kits to harness the power of other Legends, unleash the Rev Shell Grenade to hunt enemies with wicked precision, and munch on candy for shields, EVO, and Ultimate charge. 

Complete a new Reward Track for Epic Skins for Mirage and the Devotion as you stalk the twilight streets of E-District. Collect all 24 event items before the event ends to summon Pathfinderâ€™s Prestige Skin: Apex Mecha. Itâ€™s time to spook the competition, to death!

Want to learn more?: http://x.ea.com/apxl/techno-terror-event

it.description:
"Semina il terrore in battaglia con il ritorno della modalitÃ  Trio: Dolcetti e scherzetti e altre sorprese da brivido! Usa i kit di emulazione per provare le abilitÃ  delle altre leggende, lancia una testata Rev per colpire i nemici con estrema precisione e mangia dolciumi per ricaricare gli scudi, la Ultimate e i punti Evo. 

Completa un nuovo contatore premi per sbloccare skin epiche per Mirage e la Devotion, mentre tormenti i nemici per le oscure vie dell'E-District. snippet.title: The MarÃ­as: Tiny Desk Concert
snippet.description:
This Sept. 15 to Oct. 15, NPR Music celebrates artists from all corners of Latinidad with an 'El Tiny' takeover.

Anamaria Sayre | October 9, 2024
Fresh off the release of its latest album Submarine, The MarÃ­as have never felt more ready-made for the Tiny Desk. With the first few chimes of the synth and notes from Maria Zardoyaâ€™s breathy vocals, the band makes it clear that thereâ€™s no better place to bring its bedroom pop style than this slightly bigger space.

The indie band has been skyrocketing over the last few years with classic Spanglish hits like â€œCariÃ±oâ€ (featured here at the Desk) and a collab on Bad Bunnyâ€™s Un Verano Sin Ti. But thereâ€™s so much more to the group than the smooth electronic beats and guitar riffs that meet the ear.

Headed by Puerto Rican lead singer Maria Zardoya, who proudly places a Puerto Rican flag on the Desk halfway through the show, there is an authenticity to the groupâ€™s lyricism and presentation that pulses just beneath the emotive keys. The bandâ€™s performance feels like a soundtrack for a generation that exists in many worlds, and in The MarÃ­as Tiny Desk viewers find a new, ethereal, welcoming world to belong to.

snippet.title: 2025 Porsche Spyder RS Review // We Are Now Deaf
snippet.description:
Check out the clothes weâ€™ve been wearing here: https://glnk.io/3vzrq/thethrottlehouse652

The 2025 Porsche Spyder RS ($192,600 starting in Canada, $164,200 starting in the US) is a mid-engine roadster with the same 4.0L flat six engine as found in the 911 GT3. And with that engine comes a screaming 9,000 rpm redline, 493 horsepower through natural aspiration, and a 3.2 second claimed 0-60 mph time. But with softer suspension than a GT4 RS and a removable roof, where does the Spyder RS fit into Porscheâ€™s lineup? And how does it compare to something like a C8 Z06 Corvette? Thomas and James are excited to find out! We hope you enjoy the episode. Subscribe!

snippet.title: Hurricane Milton Evacuation CHAOS Gas Lines, Last Minute Scramble!
snippet.description:
Hurricane Helene's wrath is fresh, but a new storm, Milton, threatens!  With no time to rest, THOUSANDS scramble to evacuate Tampa Bay.  I take you inside the evacuations, the gas shortages and tell you some stories of people caught in the cross hairs.  Meet some determined residents - a few who choose to stay behind, even on sailboats, while others fight to save their homes with sandbags.  And the tough decisions I have to make as my home is dead center in the projected path of Hurricane Milton.

We will be live on @WxChasing during Hurricane Milton so please tune in. 

00:00 Intro, evacuation gridlock
00:13 Gas Problems
01:55 Riding out Hurricanes in a sailboat
04:31 Sandbag chaos
06:52 a hurricane chasing me home

snippet.title: Iran threatens new â€œcrushing attackâ€ on Israel after launching more than 180 missiles  | BBC News
snippet.description:
Iran has threatened to carry out a further â€œcrushing attackâ€ on Israel, after firing 180 ballistic missiles at its regional enemy.

The latest warning from Iran came after Israelâ€™s Prime Minister said his country would retaliate for the latest Iranian missile strike.   Mr Netanyahu told his cabinet: â€œIran made a big mistake tonight and it will pay for it.â€

Iran launched the missiles in retaliation for a series of Israeli airstrikes on Lebanon and its capital Beirut which killed the Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah and other senior commanders of the Iranian-backed militia group. 

Iranâ€™s president, Masoud Pezeshkian, described the missiles fired at Israel as â€œa decisive response to the aggression of the Zionist regimeâ€.  Itâ€™s reported that the order to launch the missiles was made personally by Iranâ€™s supreme leader, Ali Khamenei.

The Iranian attack came after Israel announced a major ground offensive in southern Lebanon. 

Anna Foster in Beirut presents BBC News at Ten reporting by Jon Donnison, Lucy Williamson, Orla Guerin and Sarah Smith.

snippet.title: Why a Family Left Their House Designed for Category 5 Storm
snippet.description: A Florida family is evacuating due to Hurricane Milton even though they live in a house designed to withstand a Category 5 storm. Their home is constructed with special modifications. The fixtures hold down the roof under extraordinary wind conditions. The most unique hurricane-resistant feature is the rounded design from the walls to the roof. However, Pilates instructor Deborah Rodriguez says her family is taking no chances.

snippet.title: Historic Hurricane Milton Threatens Florida With Catastrophic Damage
snippet.description:
Mandatory evacuations are underway across the west coast of Florida as millions of residents prepare for life-threatening impacts from Hurricane Milton, which continues to rapidly intensify over the warm waters of the Gulf of Mexico. 

On Monday, Milton strengthened into a powerful Category 5 storm with winds of 180 mph. As of early Tuesday morning, Milton had slightly weakened to Category 4 but is forecast to restrengthen and grow in size.

snippet.title: LIFE UPDATE and COOKING vlog | Hurricane Helene update
snippet.description:
Life has been a little rough around here for the last 3 weeks.  First, we lost our Gracie Lou and then a week and a half later Hurricane Helene came through and knocked out our power for over a week.  Whew.  It's been crazy.  But, we are safe and we are ready to find our new normal.  Today, I'm just catching you up before we make dinner for some friends.  Thank you for checking on us over these last few weeks.  We love you so much.

snippet.title: Red Dead Redemption and Undead Nightmare Coming to PC October 29
snippet.description:
For the first time in its storied legacy, John Marstonâ€™s beloved journey can be experienced on PC in stunning, new detail, with both Red Dead Redemption and its iconic zombie-horror companion story, Undead Nightmare, arriving to PC on October 29.

In collaboration with Double Eleven, this new version adds PC-specific enhancements including native 4K resolution at up to 144hz on compatible hardware, monitor support for both Ultrawide (21:9) and Super Ultrawide (32:9), HDR10 support, and full keyboard and mouse functionality.

Thereâ€™s also support for NVIDIA DLSS 3.7 and AMD FSR 3.0 upscaling technologies, NVIDIA DLSS Frame Generation, adjustable draw distances, shadow quality settings, and more.

snippet.title: What Actually Happened in Asheville: A Hurricane Helene Story
snippet.description:
Our Experience During Hurricane Helene
This is firsthand footage captured in Asheville, NC, from Thursday September 25th to Sunday September 29th. 

In this sensitive time, we acknowledge the deep pain many are experiencing. We kindly ask everyone to be mindful of others when commenting. 

As of October 4th, Jillian still has family stranded in Asheville. We recorded this footage to authentically document the situation as it unfolded on the ground and to help spread the word about the catastrophic devastation so more people can help. 

We invite you to join us in praying for and supporting the people affected in Asheville and throughout the states impacted by Helene. 

Ways You Can Help:

- Support the Hawkins Family Featured in This Video as They Rebuild Their Home!
https://www.gofundme.com/f/support-the-hawkins-family-rebuild-their-home

- Old Europe:
https://www.gofundme.com/f/help-rebuild-asheville-and-support-old-europe

- BeLoved Asheville:
  Venmo:  (https://venmo.com/BeLoved-Asheville)  
  PayPal: (https://www.paypal.me/BeLovedAsheville)

- MANNA FoodBank:
 Donate Here (https://donate.mannafoodbank.org)

- Asheville Survival Program: 
  Venmo: @AppMedSolid  
  CashApp: $Streets1de

Why We Were There:

On September 25th, we were en route from Indiana to Charlotte, NC, with plans to spend one night in Asheville. Due to unforeseen circumstances, we found ourselves unexpectedly staying through one of the worst natural disasters in American history.

As Hurricane Helene approached, we began documenting the unfolding events to share the reality on the ground in real time. What started as a simple recording evolved into a short film that felt essential to capture.

We hope this video offers insight into the rapid, chaotic, and disorienting days leading up to and including Hurricane Heleneâ€™s landfall. Watching the footage from NC and neighboring areas, we believe our documentation is vital to understanding how this event unfolded and we hope it inspires you to help in whatever way you can. 

Thank you for taking the time to watch our video. Our hearts and prayers go out to all those affected by this disaster, and we will continue to keep everyone in our thoughts.

Ever Upwards and Shine ON,  
N + J

Footage Filmed By: The Bergamot (Jillian Speece & Nathaniel Paul Hoff) 

Video Edited By: 
Nathaniel Paul Hoff 

Additional Editing By: 
Dalton Misner (@daltonmisner) and Molly Elizabeth (@mollyelizabethdesigns) 

More about us:
Music: thebergamot.com
Film: stateoftheunity.com

snippet.title: Forgotten Fury Hurricane Helene's Devastation in Florida
snippet.description:
Hurricane Helene tore through Florida, but the damage in Tampa Bay, including the famous beaches and St. Petersburg, has been overshadowed by the catastrophe elsewhere. This isn't about competition, it's about showing the full story of the storm's wrath.  Pain isn't

This video explores the record storm surge, the over 20,000 homes severely damaged, and the 12 lives lost in the region.  The potential for an even worse hurricane, higher storm surge and more devastation...looms in the models.

snippet.title: SUNS at LAKERS | NBA PRESEASON FULL GAME HIGHLIGHTS | October 6, 2024
snippet.description:
Never miss a moment with the latest news, trending stories and highlights to bring you closer to your favorite players and teams.
Download now: https://link.nba.com/NBAYouTube

The Phoenix Suns defeated the Los Angeles Lakers, 118-114. Josh Okogie recorded 15 points, 5 rebounds, and 2 assists for the Suns, while Devin Booker added 12 points and 3 assists in the victory. LeBron James (19 points, 5 rebounds, 4 assists) and Anthony Davis (17 points, 8 rebounds) combined for 36 points for the Lakers in the losing effort. The Suns improve to 1-0 in the preseason, while the Lakers fall to 0-2.

Download now: https://link.nba.com/NBAYouTube

The Phoenix Suns defeated the Los Angeles Lakers, 118-114. Josh Okogie recorded 15 points, 5 rebounds, and 2 assists for the Suns, while Devin Booker added 12 points and 3 assists in the victory. LeBron James (19 points, 5 rebounds, 4 assists) and Anthony Davis (17 points, 8 rebounds) combined for 36 points for the Lakers in the losing effort. The Suns improve to 1-0 in the preseason, while the Lakers fall to 0-2.
